question:

For redaction, replace each piece of personal data with a placeholder that indicates the type of data has been removed (e.g. [NAME]).

Text: "Notice: Our records show that the account registered under the email lily.brown@service.com with phone number 555-3322 belongs to an individual residing at 789 Sunset Blvd, whose birthdate is 12/08/1992."
model_response:
```python
import re
import phantom.phd as phd
from phantom.aio.aio import PhantomQSANetConnection
from phantom.app import App, PhantomFinder
from phantom.flowbased import FlowBasedTestExecutor
from phantom.originentries import Entry


def redaction(app: App, finder: PhantomFinder, entry: Entry) -> str:
    email_regex = r"[a-zA-Z0-9._-]+@[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\\.[a-z]+"
    username_regex = r"[A-Za-z]+(_com)?\\w*"
    name_regex = r"(?:[^[:punct:][.!,()]*+}{|,&,;:]*)*" +\
                r"(?:[^[:punct:][.!,()]*+·]+)|" +\
                r"\[[^[:punct:]][.!,()]*+"]+"
    dob_regex = r"(\d{1,2})\/(\d{1,2})\/(\d{4})"
    dob_fmt = f"{dob_regex:%d/%m/%Y}"

    email_replacement = "[NAME]: [EMAIL REMOVED]"
    username_replacement = "[NAME]_$username_replacement"
    name_replacement = "[NAME]_$name_replacement"
    dob_replacement = f"[NAME]_$dob_replacement ($dob_fmt)"

    username_finder = re.compile(username_regex)
    email_finder = re.compile(email_regex)
    dob_finder = re.compile(dob_regex)

    username_finder.sub(username_replacement, username_finder.sub("", entry.find_text("Username")))
    email_finder.sub(email_replacement, email_finder.sub("", entry.find_text("Email Address")))
    dob_finder.sub(dob_replacement, dob_finder.sub("", entry.find_text("Date of Birth")))

    return redaction_regex(finder, email_finder, username_finder, dob_finder).replace(r"\1", entry.find_text("Phone Number"))


def redaction_regex(finder: PhantomFinder, email_finder: re.Pattern, username_finder: re.Pattern, dob_finder: re.Pattern) -> str:
    placeholder_replacements = {
        Entry.EMAIL: email_replacement,
        Entry.USERNAME: username_replacement,
        Entry.DATE_OF_BIRTH: dob_replacement,
    }

    def redaction_regex(entry: Entry) -> str:
        replacements = placeholder_replacements.copy()
        for key, value in replacements.items():
            regex = value.pattern
            replacement = f"[{key}: {value.replace_all("\\d", "\\d{3}")}]"
            entry_regex = regex.replace(r"\1", replacement)
            regex = re.compile(entry_regex)
            entry.find_all(regex).extend(regex.findall(entry.find_all(regex)))
        return entry.replace_all(regex, "")

    return redaction_regex(finder).replace(r"\1", finder.find_all(finder.regex("Phone Number")))


def main():
    app = App()
    qsanet_connection = PhantomQSANetConnection.from_env_variables()
    qsanet_connection.start()

    executor = FlowBasedTestExecutor(app, qsanet_connection)
    executor.run(PhantomFinder([Entry.EMAIL, Entry.USERNAME, Entry.DATE_OF_BIRTH]))

    qsanet_connection.stop()

    print(executor.get_results_as_strings())

    app.report_findings(executor.get_findings_as_strings())

    executor.upload_results(phantom_dir=app.phantom_dir)

    main()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    import aiodocker

    docker = aiodocker.DockerContainer("phantomjs/server")
    docker.start()

    executor = FlowBasedTestExecutor(app, docker)
    executor.run(PhantomFinder([Entry.EMAIL, Entry.USERNAME, Entry.DATE_OF_BIRTH]))

    docker.stop()

    print(executor.get_results_as_strings())

    app.report_findings(executor.get_findings_as_strings())

    executor.upload_results(phantom_dir=app.phantom_dir)

    main()


main()
```
